From $716.9B of net sales to $80.0B of operating income, FY2025 (US$ billions).
:::
:::


A couple of things jump out. **Cost of sales** (≈50% of revenue) is the physical
reality of being a retailer — the goods themselves and shipping. But notice
**technology & infrastructure**: at ~$109B it has nearly caught up with
**fulfillment** (~$109B) and is the fastest-growing line, reflecting the capex
and depreciation behind AWS and the current AI build-out.

