Amazon (AMZN) daily close, last 5 years. Pulled live via yfinance at render time.
:::
:::


The daily chart is noise on top of signal, though. To see what actually drives
the price over years rather than days, the right lens is **per-share metrics** —
because an investor doesn't own "Amazon," they own a *share* of it.

### Revenue per share vs. earnings per share

Two KPIs matter to a shareholder: how much **revenue** and how much **profit**
the business generates *per share they hold*. (The "per share" part isn't
cosmetic — share count drifts up over time as stock-based compensation dilutes
existing holders, a quiet headwind to per-share growth. Amazon's diluted share
count rose ~5% over this window.)

